anxious: feel anxious, be anxious, gets a bit anxious
When I feel anxious, I'm worried about something bad will happen

I get a bit anxious before taking an exam, but I manage it.

awful: be awful, feel awful, look awful
When something is awful, it is very bad
Because of the awful traffic, I was late for the meeting / I arrived late to the meeting.
I got stuck in awful traffic, which made me late for the meeting.
Because he did poorly on the math exam, he did not qualify for the next round.

traffic: awful traffic, terrible traffic, heavy traffic

consist of
to be composed or made up of
I will have a group assignment next week. My group consists of two boys and two girls.

desire
want something, especially strongly
I desire a better-paying job and a a more structured work environment
I'm looking for a better-paying job with a more structured work environment

eager
when a person is eager about sth, they are execited about it
His eager participation in volunteer activities made him well-liked by everyone

well-like = popular

household = a group of people, often a family, live together
My family consists of my father, my mother and me. So we have a small household
